name: Subliminal Metamorphosis (2021)
description: "Their true meaning lies in the mind of the beholder." This artwork by Sanning Arkitekter represents the disposition of the human psyche to conjure meaningful interpretations from ambiguous matters. Whether adhering to the theoretical assumptions of Swiss psychoanalyst Hermann Rorschach or not, the ambiguous nature of the inkblots in continuous shapeshifting invites the observer to, in his or her unique way, interpret the metamorphosis, and they themselves give meaning to the artwork.
